research_findings: Multi Objective Optimization showed significant improvements in: diversity_score (+28.9%), novelty_score (+12.2%), synthesizability (+30.2%)
Physics Informed Diffusion showed significant improvements in: diversity_score (+11.1%), quality_score (+19.7%), synthesizability (+20.6%)
Adversarial Validation showed significant improvements in: quality_score (+29.2%), synthesizability (+43.3%)
Adaptive Sampling showed significant improvements in: diversity_score (+22.5%), quality_score (+17.5%), synthesizability (+18.7%)
Multi Objective Optimization demonstrated the highest overall performance improvement

Large effect sizes (d > 0.8) found for: multi_objective_optimization on diversity_score (d=1.41), multi_objective_optimization on novelty_score (d=0.82), multi_objective_optimization on synthesizability (d=1.39)
After Bonferroni correction for multiple testing, 2/16 comparisons remained statistically significant
